OL,3,CWhat is Plato - the operation declared
OL,4,Cafter stabbing at Manchester synagogue?
OL,6,FA "marauding terror attack" (MTA) is
OL,7,Fdefined by the National Protective
OL,8,FSecurity Authority (NPSA - the UK's
OL,9,Fgovernment body relating to national
OL,10,Fsecurity and counter-terrorism) as any
OL,11,Fviolent incident "where assailants
OL,12,Fmove through a location aiming to find
OL,13,Fand kill or injure as many people as
OL,14,Fpossible".
OL,16,FMTAs aim to harm as many people as
OL,17,Fpossible in a short space of time and
OL,18,Ftypically involve the use of weapons
OL,19,Fsuch as knives, firearms or vehicles.
